American rapper, Jay Jenkins, popularly known as Jeezy, and his wife, Jeannie Mai, have welcomed their first child together. The new mum, who is also a Television host and fashion mogul, made the announcement on her verified Instagram page on Tuesday night. Sharing a picture of her child’s hospital cot, the first-time mum wrote, ” I asked God for a life of love and happiness. He sent me my family. Baby Jenkins is here.” The couple had in September 2021 announced that they were expecting their first child together. The Real co-host and rapper began dating in 2018 but got married in March 2021. Though Jeezy had never been married, he has three children prior to his marriage to the TV host. Mai, however, had been previously married to Freddy Harteis but the couple split after ten years. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com